The paper deals with a manipulation task for personal robots, which involves placing objects in unstructured environments. This task requires the robot to learn to handle new object types and new placing areas. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed algorithm uses point-clouds of the object and the placing area, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The algorithm is based on supervised learning, which involves training a model to predict good placements. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with a real-world application of the algorithm, which involves controlling a personal robot. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
